    <div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"><p dir="ltr">Cleaning up is one of the advantages of working with VMs over a bare metal install. Since everything is in the disk image files, we only need to delete the VM. Vagrant provides two commands for this purpose:</p>
<h4 dir="ltr">Stopping and Deleting the VM</h4>
<p dir="ltr">Change to the directory containing the Vagrantfile, and then stop the VM:</p>
<p dir="ltr">vagrant halt</p>
<p dir="ltr">To delete the VM permanently:</p>
<p dir="ltr">vagrant destroy</p>
